Thirteen suspected members of Boko Haram have been arrested by troops in Kano. The suspects were apprehended in the Filin Lazio, Hotoro area of the state, the Army said. A statement by Director, Army Public Relations Brigadier General Mohammed Yerima said, “In an ongoing effort to flush out all forms of criminality within its area of responsibility, troops of 3 Brigade Nigerian Army have arrested 13 suspected Boko Haram terrorists around  Filin Lazio, Hotoro axis of Kano State on Saturday 8 May 2021. “The ongoing operations is predicated on the need to apprehend criminals who may want to hibernate in any part of Kano State. “The Nigerian Army wishes to use this medium to appeal to the peace loving people of Kano State to maintain high level of vigilance and continue to report suspected movement of strange individuals or groups in their environment to the relevant security agencies for prompt action.”